# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   For an app, this is usually fine to prevent conflicts.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a windows/mac/linux mixture, you might want to ignore it.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

